children.subject:
That's definitely a hard schedule, but given your experience with those other 3 classes it should definitely be doable. For context I took 170 + 126 + 16b last fall and it was difficult but doable.

I'd also, for 16b, be more concerned about forgetting circuit knowledge from 16a rather than forgetting lin alg knowledge.

I would be very careful. You are taking three techs, however those three are normally considered to be the 3 easiest techs, and you are looking at taking three of the hardest. In particular you might want to try to take 16b before taking 126

16b was sooo time-consuming for me when I took it. Same with 162. I also was not the strongest when taking 70 (though I ended up with an A) and 126 was a great class, but it's definitely much harder if you don't already understand a lot of it. Would not recommend this schedule unless you're really willing to put in a TON of time

history.content: I want to take 127 + 189 in the spring, and at least 162 in the fall. However, I feel my probability knowledge is not that strong (A- in 70), so I also want to take 126. However, I still have not taken 16b, and I feel like I basically forgot all the linalg taught in 16a. Would 162 + 126 + 16b be a really hard schedule? I am currently taking 161 + 188 + 186 and it is pretty manageable.
history.subject: 162 + 126 + 16b?
